City of Mist. Ive never been there and thought i would ask questions first.<br>
<br>
Are there regular groups there? Is it a primary raid only place? good for what levels? (lowest to highest)<br>
<br>
Sorry for the inconveniance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukallikamerov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalli Kamerov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 476<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/26/01 11:43:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959015.jpg width = 135 height = 184></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: CoM question</span><hr size=1> I've done a few reaver raids and it seems that there's almost always 1 group ~ level 40 sitting right at the zone.<br>
<br>
A single group with a rogue and a decent puller could do the area around the first reaver pretty easily around 50th or so, though the first reaver himself would probably be a bit much for anything less than a group of ~ 55's. (magic immune, when you kill him either another reaver or a tougher lord pops out... will just wear down a single group over time).<br>
<br>
There's a few spots in there other groups could get to, but I don't think pickup groups ever form around there....<br>
<br>
Kalli Kamerov<br>
55th Enchantress<br>
Poison Arrow<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujasiofneriak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jasi of Neriak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/27/01 12:41:27 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ang.mux.net/smjasi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: CoM question</span><hr size=1> City of Mist's front areas are great for Mid 30's to Mid 40's. But, you may not always be able to get a group there, and it's a bit out of the way. It helps to at least bring a partial group with you. :)<br>
<br>
You're also going to want to educate yourself a little on the zone, and be very cautious when first getting started. Pathing can be FREAKY. Tell your casters to avoid AoE spells since you could agro something in the wall that's going to have to go three miles out of the way, agroing everything else it meets, before it gets to you to pound your tushie. Trains can be NASTY.  Nothing like the constant stream of express engines in Karnors, Mistmoore or Unrest, but deadly just the same. :)<br>
<br>
One time, I was there with a solid guild group. Enchanter, Cleric, Monk, Warrior, myself (rogue ;) and probably a druid. We'd been pulling and fighting near the back of the zone for a little while and doing quite well. Suddenly, with no warning, there were about 17 mobs surrounding us. As you can imagine, wipe out. Something in the wall got agro'd and everything between them and us charged. We were probably lucky we didn't have a Reaver tag along for the ride.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong... CoM is great hunting, and awesome exp. Melee types can also bind there, which is a bonus for the long run it takes to get there. BUT, it's a place to be careful of, and don't count on a casual pick-up group every time you show up. :)<br>
<br>
Anyway. I've babbled enough.<br>
<br>
Jasi<br>
Hollow Omen<br>
Cuisinart of Doom<br>
52nd Level Rogue <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=470.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=480.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.threadControl?topicID=479.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=479.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=479.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (Admin only)<option value="brellserilisfrm64">Archived Threads<option value="brellserilismeleetalk">Tome: Races and Classes <option value="brellserilisroleplaying">Tome: History of Norrath<option value="brellserilisfrm49">Tome: Visions of Norrath<option value="brellserilisfr